 &=\int_{0}^{1}\left( \frac{x^2}{2}+x\right)dx= \frac{1}{6}+ \frac{1}{2}= \frac{2}{3}.
\end{align*}$$

\begin{center}
\shadowbox{
$\displaystyle\iint_{D}(x+y)\;dxdy= \frac{2}{3}$.
